This ruin seems to be infested with thugs, woof!
Stop with the lazy speech endings.

This is the Recollection Room! It will be unlocked once
you've seen at least one ending.

I'm a veteran adventurer! Let me teach you newbies something
good.

If you initiate combat from behind a monster, you can get a
preemptive attack.

Plus, your friends have got your back, so it's rare to be
caught off guard by an enemy.

If you're defeated by minor enemies, there won't be a defeat
H-scene! You'll be sent back home, but it won't be game
over, so rest easy.

Remember that you can use items during battle faster than
the monsters can act!

If you're in a pinch, use an item to heal before the enemy
can attack you.
If you want to avoid battle, choose to escape.

Escape is guaranteed to succeed, so feel free to run away
from annoying enemies!

The girl with purple hair seems to have the makings of an
attacker. She also seems good at inflicting status ailments.
Battles against monsters can go smoothly if you inflict
status ailments on them!

The girl with yellow hair seems to be good at magic! She's
probably not great at physical attacks, so it's best to
always use magic. As she levels up, she'll learn powerful
spells one after another.

To change characters in the status, skill, or equipment
screen, press 'Q Key' or 'W Key'!
